fd = 0 (stdin)&lt;br/&gt;
fd = 1 (stdout)&lt;br/&gt;
fd = 2 (stderr)

we want to write on `stdout`.

the second argument is your string that you want to print
and count is the size of the print string.

small example:

```
#include &lt;unistd.h&gt;
#include &lt;string.h&gt;

void main (void) {
    const char * string = &quot;test&quot;;

    write(1, string, strlen(string));
}
```

